author: Marcus Cho
title: Nike’s Air Max 90 Flyknit Is Getting a “Multicolor” Colorway
text:
Visit the original post to see all 4 images from this gallery. 
Not too long after we got a glimpse of Nike’s upcoming Air Max 90 Flyknit “Infrared” colorway , we’re now getting another look at a new “Multicolor” edition.
While some editions of Nike’s “Multicolor” line feature Flyknit weaves that lean more towards pink or green, sneakerheads will rejoice to find that this particular edition offers a balanced rainbow of colors, interrupted only by hits of black on the mudguard and sockliner, and blue on the Nike Swoosh. The look is wrapped up by a white midsole and metallic silver elements on the heel and eyelets.
The Nike Air Max 90 Flyknit “Multicolor” is officially set to debut March 2.
